    "slug": "cracking-the-unit-economics-of-tech-first-ivf-in-tier-2-india",
    "title": "Cracking the Unit Economics of Tech-First IVF in Tier-2 India",
    "excerpt": "As the Indian fertility market continues to grow, with over 300,000–350,000 IVF cycles performed annually, the need for efficient and cost-effective solutions has never been more p...",
    "html": "<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*DwtufWzVkaSrxtzmF_6fEw.png\"></figure><p>As the Indian fertility market continues to grow, with over 300,000–350,000 IVF cycles performed annually, the need for efficient and cost-effective solutions has never been more pressing.</p>\n<p>Recent trends signal a shift towards tech-first approaches in healthcare, with investors backing digital health platforms that can scale and optimise unit economics.</p>\n<h4><strong>The Challenge of Unit Economics in IVF</strong></h4>\n<p>Traditionally, IVF chains have struggled to maintain profitability due to high operational costs, low patient volumes, and inadequate technology infrastructure.</p>\n<p>However, by leveraging AI-powered embryo selection, telemedicine-led patient funnels, and standardised protocols, tech-first IVF chains can significantly reduce costs per cycle and improve outcomes.</p>\n<h4><strong>Key Drivers of Unit Economics in Tech-First IVF</strong></h4>\n<p>• <strong>AI embryo selection:</strong> Reduces the need for manual intervention, minimising errors and enhancing cycle success rates</p>\n<p>• <strong>Telemedicine-first patient funnel:</strong> Increases patient acquisition and retention, while decreasing operational costs associated with physical infrastructure</p>\n<p>• <strong>Standardised protocols:</strong> Ensures consistency in treatment outcomes, reducing variability and improving overall efficiency</p>\n<h4><strong>The Opportunity in Tier-2 India</strong></h4>\n<p>With a vast and underserved market, tier-2 India presents a fertile ground for tech-first IVF chains to establish a strong presence.</p>\n<p>By focusing on this region, <strong>Santaan Fertility </strong>aims to capitalise on the growing demand for fertility treatments, while optimising unit economics through a tech-first approach.</p>\n<h4><strong>Unlocking Growth in Tier-2 India</strong></h4>\n<p><strong>• Scalable technology infrastructure:</strong> Enables the efficient expansion of services to new locations, without compromising on quality or outcomes</p>\n<p>• <strong>Empathy-driven patient acquisition:</strong> Builds trust and loyalty among patients, driving retention and word-of-mouth referrals</p>\n<p>• <strong>Research and development:</strong> Continuously improves treatment protocols and outcomes, reinforcing the chain’s competitive advantage</p>\n<p><strong>Connect With Us</strong></p>\n<p>For Clinicians: Join our Santaan network</p>\n<p>👉 Contact our Clinical Relations Team</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://santaan.in/contact-us\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/contact-us</a></p>\n<p><strong>Technical Metadata</strong></p>",
    "publishedAt": "2026-03-30 08:19:22",
    "author": "Santaan Fertility Center and Research Institute",
    "thumbnail": "https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*DwtufWzVkaSrxtzmF_6fEw.png",
