    "title": "PGT-A Testing in Bhubaneswar: Preventing Recurrent Miscarriage",
    "excerpt": "Struggling with repeated IVF failures or early losses? Learn how PGT-A testing at Santaan checks the embryo’s genetic blueprint. Transparent pricing & 0% EMI available. The Story: ...",
    "html": "<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*PRcqMWO8rXMlmomXNS5t6A.png\"></figure><p>Struggling with repeated IVF failures or early losses? Learn how <a href=\"https://ivf.santaan.in/\"><strong>PGT-A testing</strong></a> at Santaan checks the embryo’s genetic blueprint. Transparent pricing &amp; 0% EMI available.</p>\n<h4><strong>The Story: Kalyani’s Unseen Heartbreak</strong></h4>\n<p>Kalyani and her husband, Subrata, from the coal-rich town of Angul, Odisha, were exhausted. To the world, Kalyani was a pillar of strength, managing her family’s large household. But inside, she carried the heavy, silent grief of three early miscarriages.</p>\n<p>During her last IVF cycle at another clinic, the doctor told her the embryos were “Grade A- perfect.” Yet, within six weeks, the pregnancy slipped away again. The village elders whispered about “bad stars” and “evil eyes,” making Kalyani feel that her womb was somehow cursed. She didn’t realise that the “soil” was perfectly fine. The issue lay hidden deep inside the “seed”, an invisible error in the blueprint that no standard microscope could see.</p>\n<h4><strong>The Clinical Truth: The “Beautiful Apple” Illusion</strong></h4>\n<p>In traditional IVF, embryologists choose which embryo to transfer based on how it looks. But an embryo can look perfectly round and healthy on the outside while carrying the wrong amount of genetic information (chromosomes) on the inside.</p>\n<p>Think of a beautifully bound book that has pages missing inside. If an embryo has missing or extra chromosomes (a condition called Aneuploidy), nature’s safety mechanism will gently stop the pregnancy from continuing. This is the single most common cause of recurrent miscarriages and unexplained IVF failures, especially for women over 32.</p>\n<h4><strong>The Santaan Difference: Reading the Blueprint with PGT-A &amp; XAI</strong></h4>\n<p>At Santaan, recognised as the <a href=\"https://ivf.santaan.in/\"><strong>best fertility clinic in Odisha</strong></a>, we don’t just rely on how a seed looks; we read its blueprint.</p>\n<p>Using Preimplantation Genetic Testing for Aneuploidies (PGT-A), our embryologists gently take 3–4 microscopic cells from the outer shell of the embryo (the part that becomes the placenta, leaving the baby untouched.) We test these cells to ensure there are exactly 46 healthy chromosomes.</p>\n<p>When we combine this genetic map with our XAI (Explainable AI), which tracks the embryo’s exact growth patterns, we can select the one “golden seed” destined to thrive. This drastically reduces the risk of miscarriage and brings joy to families seeking recurrent miscarriage treatment in Bhubaneswar.</p>\n<p>Because advanced technology should not be a luxury, we offer Transparent Pricing for PGT-A testing, paired with flexible 0% EMI options, ensuring your journey to a healthy baby is both scientifically and financially secure.</p>\n<h4><strong>FAQ</strong></h4>\n<p><strong>1. What is PGT-A, and who needs it?</strong></p>\n<p>PGT-A is a genetic test performed on embryos during an IVF cycle to check for chromosomal abnormalities. It is highly recommended for women over 35, couples with a history of recurrent miscarriages, or those who have experienced multiple failed IVF cycles despite having “good quality” embryos.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Does PGT-A harm the embryo?</strong></p>\n<p>No. The biopsy is performed by highly trained senior embryologists using precision lasers. They only remove a few cells from the trophectoderm (the outer layer that eventually forms the placenta), leaving the inner cell mass (which becomes the baby) completely untouched and safe.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Is PGT-A testing affordable with EMI options?</strong></p>\n<p>Yes. At Santaan, we believe in Transparent Pricing with no hidden laboratory fees. We offer 0% EMI options to help families access <a href=\"https://ivf.santaan.in/\"><strong>advanced PGT-A testing</strong></a> without the burden of upfront financial stress.</p>\n<p><strong>Stop leaving your dream to chance.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>If you have faced repeated heartbreak, let’s read the blueprint together.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>WhatsApp us at: </strong>+91- 81051 08416</p>\n<p><strong>Publishing Metadata</strong></p>\n<p>Published from @santaanIVF</p>\n<p>Tags: #audience-patient #IVFSuccess recurrent miscarriage treatment in Bhubaneswar, best fertility clinic in Odisha, PGT-A testing in India, IVF success rates.</p>\n<p>Internal Links:</p>\n<p>Precision IVF Protocols at Santaan: <a href=\"https://santaan.in/ivf-treatment\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/ivf-treatment</a></p>\n<p>AI-Driven Embryology Technology: <a href=\"https://santaan.in/technology\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/technology</a></p>\n<p>Read our previous blogs: <a href=\"https://santaan.in/fertility-insights\">https://santaan.in/fertility-insights</a></p>",
