    "slug": "ai-in-ivf-2026-polygenic-risk-scores-pgt-p-ethics-non-invasive-deepembryo-analytics-and",
    "title": "AI in IVF 2026: Polygenic Risk Scores (PGT-P) Ethics, Non-Invasive ‘DeepEmbryo’ Analytics, and…",
    "excerpt": "AI in IVF 2026: Polygenic Risk Scores (PGT-P) Ethics, Non-Invasive ‘DeepEmbryo’ Analytics, and Ectopic Risk Prediction Clinical Disclaimer: For clinician education only; not patien...",
    "html": "<h3><strong>AI in IVF 2026: Polygenic Risk Scores (PGT-P) Ethics, Non-Invasive ‘DeepEmbryo’ Analytics, and Ectopic Risk Prediction</strong></h3>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*r4CkeQnG5jEKIGBF3P2RKg.png\"></figure><p><strong>Clinical Disclaimer:</strong> For clinician education only; not patient-specific medical advice.</p>\n<p>Welcome to the March 18, 2026, edition of Fertility Insights. Today, we navigate the complex ethical and scientific frontier of Polygenic Risk Scoring (PGT-P), explore the latest validation of DeepEmbryo (a non-invasive AI assessment tool), and review data-driven insights on ectopic pregnancy prediction and metabolic health during FET cycles.</p>\n<h4><strong>🔬 Clinical Update: The PGT-P Debate &amp; March 2026 ASRM Opinion</strong></h4>\n<p>The clinical utility of Polygenic Risk Testing for embryos (PGT-P) remains a focal point of discussion this month. The ASRM Ethics and Practice Committees recently issued a formal opinion regarding the screening of embryos for multifactorial diseases like hypertension, type 2 diabetes, and certain cancers.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Key Finding:</strong> The report concludes that PGT-P is not yet ready for clinical practice due to “predictive uncertainties” and the significant ethical risks of overstating what polygenic risk scores can reliably determine.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Mechanism:</strong> Current models are limited by an incomplete understanding of gene-environment interactions and a lack of diverse genomic representation. Polygenic risk scoring accounts for only a small percentage of clinical variation, as lifestyle factors post-birth significantly impact these outcomes.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Evidence Level:</strong> High (Consensus Committee Opinion).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Use of preimplantation genetic testing for polygenic disorders (PGT-P): an Ethics Committee opinion (2026),” ASRM Practice Guidance (2026).</p>\n<h4><strong>🤖 DeepEmbryo: Non-Invasive Prediction via Static Imaging</strong></h4>\n<p>While time-lapse imaging (TLI) is a gold standard, many labs still rely on static snapshots. DeepEmbryo, a new AI-based assessment algorithm, has demonstrated the ability to predict pregnancy outcomes with high accuracy using just three static images.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Performance:</strong> In recent internal validation studies (March 2026), “Fusion models” that integrate blastocyst images with patient clinical data (age, AMH, history) achieved an accuracy of 82.4% and an AUC of 0.91.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Clinical Utility:</strong> DeepEmbryo allows labs without expensive TLI hardware to benefit from AI-supported selection by automating the segmentation of embryo parts (ICM, TE, Zona) and identifying subtle growth patterns linked to implantation success.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Explore our AI-Driven Lab Infrastructure at Santaan.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “An artificial intelligence algorithm to select most viable embryos considering current process in IVF labs,” Frontiers in AI (2024/2026 Update) / PMID: [400722468].</p>\n<h4><strong>📉 Ectopic Risk Analytics &amp; FET Metabolic Health</strong></h4>\n<p>The March 2026 episode of Fertility and Sterility On Air highlights new research into predicting ectopic pregnancy (EP) and the role of exercise in Frozen Embryo Transfer (FET) success.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Ectopic Prediction:</strong> New dynamic prediction models using longitudinal serum hCG and progesterone ratios are helping clinicians triage “Pregnancy of Unknown Location” (PUL) cases more effectively. AI models now distinguish between successful methotrexate outcomes and surgical risks with improved specificity.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Exercise &amp; FET:</strong> Evidence suggests that moderate-intensity exercise (150 mins/week) significantly improves insulin sensitivity and energy balance, positively correlating with higher live birth rates during FET cycles, provided it is not performed to the point of exhaustion.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Learn about Santaan’s Precision Ovarian Stimulation Protocols.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Fertility and Sterility On Air — TOC: March 2026,” ASRM Podcasts (2026).</p>\n<h4><strong>📈 Santaan’s Scientific Leadership</strong></h4>\n<p>At Santaan, we emphasize Transparency. Whether navigating the complexities of polygenic screening or implementing non-invasive AI grading, our “Human-in-the-Loop” philosophy ensures that technology serves as a decision-support tool, not a replacement for clinical intuition. For more technical briefings, follow us on Santaan IVF on Medium.</p>\n<p><strong>Connect With Us</strong></p>\n<p><strong>For Clinicians:</strong> Collaborate with the leaders in digital health. Are you interested in the data behind our AI-driven receptivity mapping or our PGT-A triage protocols?</p>\n<p>👉 Contact our Clinical Relations Team</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://santaan.in/contact-us\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/contact-us</a></p>\n<p><strong>Technical Metadata</strong></p>",
