    "excerpt": "AI in IVF 2026: Multi-Dimensional Composite Scoring, Personalised Ovarian Response Curves, and the STAR Method for Azoospermia Disclaimer: For clinician education only; not patient...",
    "html": "<h3><strong>AI in IVF 2026: Multi-Dimensional Composite Scoring, Personalised Ovarian Response Curves, and the STAR Method for Azoospermia</strong></h3>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*qUETtWtZzgw1D0bp2DmhVw.png\"></figure><p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> For clinician education only; not patient-specific medical advice.</p>\n<p>Welcome to the March 13, 2026, edition of Fertility Insights. As the reproductive landscape shifts toward high-precision digital health, Santaan remains committed to translating the latest AI breakthroughs into superior clinical outcomes. Today, we move beyond standalone embryo grading to examine Multi-Dimensional Composite Scoring, the clinical validation of Personalised Ovarian Response (NOR) AI, and a paradigm-shifting method for sperm recovery.</p>\n<h4><strong>🔬 Clinical Deep Dive: The CS = (EQS + ERS)/2 Framework</strong></h4>\n<p>The most significant evolution in early 2026 is the transition from isolated embryo selection to Composite Scoring (CS). A landmark study published in Frontiers in Artificial Intelligence (2026) validates a framework that integrates embryo quality with automated endometrial receptivity.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Mechanism:</strong> The system uses a U-Net CNN with a VGG16 encoder backbone for automated endometrial segmentation, extracting thickness and trilaminar patterns from ultrasound. This is combined with an AI-derived Embryo Quality Score (EQS).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Evidence Level:</strong> High (Validation shows an AUC of 0.94 for biochemical pregnancy, significantly outperforming standalone embryo or uterine markers).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Clinical Value:</strong> At a cutoff of CS ≥ 6.5, the model reached 92.1% sensitivity, offering a robust tool for “Freeze-All” decision support when the uterine environment is suboptimal.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Artificial intelligence models and combined scoring approaches for endometrial receptivity assessment,” Frontiers in AI (2026) / DOI: 10.3389/frai.2025.1673800.</p>\n<h4><strong>🤖 InOvaSGuide: Personalised Dose-Response AI</strong></h4>\n<p>Standardising the starting dose of FSH is being revolutionised by the InOvaSGuide prototype, an integrated framework for predicting Ovarian Response (NOR) and OHSS risk simultaneously.</p>\n<p>• <strong>The Innovation:</strong> Rather than a static dose based on weight or AMH, the AI generates Individualised Dose-Response Curves. These curves display the predicted number of oocytes and the probability of moderate-to-severe OHSS across a range of FSH doses.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Performance:</strong> Recent multicenter evaluations show that AI-assisted dosing matched or exceeded REI performance in 76% of cases, particularly in preventing over-stimulation in high-responders.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Explore our Precision Ovarian Stimulation Protocols.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Integrated Prediction System for Individualised Ovarian Stimulation and OHSS Prevention,” JMIR (2026) / PMID: [41229699].</p>\n<h4><strong>🧬 The STAR Method: AI-Guided Sperm Recovery for Azoospermia</strong></h4>\n<p>For patients with non-obstructive azoospermia (NOA), finding a single viable sperm cell is often impossible manually. The STAR (Sperm Tracking and Recovery) system, recently reported in The Lancet and Columbia University Research, has achieved its first successful clinical pregnancy in a couple trying for 19 years.</p>\n<p>• <strong>The Breakthrough:</strong> The system scans approximately 2.5 million images from a sample in just 2 hours. In a clinical case where manual slide examination revealed no sperm, the STAR system detected seven sperm cells (two motile and five non-motile).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Outcome:</strong> The two motile sperm were injected via ICSI, leading to successful embryo formation and a positive pregnancy test.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Discover Santaan’s Advanced AI-Driven Lab Technology.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “How AI helped an infertile couple conceive after 19 years with just ‘2 sperm’,” The Lancet / Economic Times (2026).</p>\n<h4><strong>📈 Santaan’s Scientific Leadership</strong></h4>\n<p>At Santaan, we emphasise Explainable AI (XAI). We don’t just provide a score; we provide the biological rationale, such as heatmap-based saliency mapping, to ensure clinicians maintain the “Human-in-the-Loop” for every decision. For a technical deep dive into our U-Net architectures and STAR recovery protocols, visit: Santaan IVF on Medium.</p>\n<p><strong>Connect With Us</strong></p>\n<p><strong>For Clinicians:</strong> Stay at the forefront of reproductive science. Join our collaborative network to access real-time AI-driven benchmarks and advanced diagnostic support for male-factor cases.</p>\n<p>👉 Contact our Clinical Relations Team</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://santaan.in/contact-us\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/contact-us</a></p>\n<p><strong>Technical Metadata</strong></p>",
