    "slug": "ai-in-ivf-2026-composite-receptivity-scoring-personalised-dose-response-curves-and-metabolomic",
    "title": "AI in IVF 2026: Composite Receptivity Scoring, Personalised Dose-Response Curves, and Metabolomic…",
    "excerpt": "AI in IVF 2026: Composite Receptivity Scoring, Personalised Dose-Response Curves, and Metabolomic SCM Profiling Clinical Disclaimer: For clinician education only; not patient-speci...",
    "html": "<h3><strong>AI in IVF 2026: Composite Receptivity Scoring, Personalised Dose-Response Curves, and Metabolomic SCM Profiling</strong></h3>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*EsQ4HwucCnfs6m_HUac6QA.png\"></figure><p><strong>Clinical Disclaimer:</strong> For clinician education only; not patient-specific medical advice.</p>\n<p>Welcome to the March 10, 2026, edition of Fertility Insights. As the reproductive landscape shifts toward high-precision digital health, Santaan remains committed to translating the latest AI breakthroughs into superior clinical outcomes. Today, we move beyond standalone embryo grading to examine Multi-Dimensional Composite Scoring, the clinical launch of Personalised Dose-Response AI for stimulation, and the latest meta-analysis on Spent Culture Media (SCM) metabolic biomarkers.</p>\n<h4><strong>🔬 Clinical Deep Dive: The CS = (EQS + ERS)/2 Framework</strong></h4>\n<p>The most significant shift in early 2026 is the transition from isolated embryo selection to Composite Scoring (CS). A landmark study published in Frontiers in Artificial Intelligence (March 2026) validates a framework that integrates embryo quality with automated endometrial receptivity.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Mechanism:</strong> The system uses a U-Net CNN with a VGG16 backbone for automated endometrial segmentation, extracting thickness and trilaminar patterns. This is mathematically combined with an AI-derived Embryo Quality Score (EQS) and SART clinical probability data.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Evidence Level:</strong> High (Internal validation shows an AUC of 0.94 for biochemical pregnancy, significantly outperforming standalone embryo or uterine markers).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Clinical Value:</strong> At an optimal cutoff of CS ≥ 6.5, the model reached a 92.1% sensitivity and 91.0% positive predictive value (PPV), offering a robust tool for “Freeze-All” decision support when the uterine environment is suboptimal.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Artificial intelligence models and combined scoring approaches for endometrial receptivity assessment,” Frontiers in AI (March 2026) / DOI: 10.3389/frai.2025.1673800.</p>\n<h4><strong>🤖 InOvaSGuide: Personalised Dose-Response AI</strong></h4>\n<p>Standardising the starting dose of FSH is being revolutionised by the InOvaSGuide prototype, an integrated framework for predicting Ovarian Response (NOR) and OHSS risk simultaneously.</p>\n<p>• <strong>The Innovation:</strong> Rather than a static dose based on weight or AMH, the AI generates Individualised Dose-Response Curves. These curves display the predicted number of oocytes and the probability of moderate-to-severe OHSS across a range of FSH doses.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Performance:</strong> Recent multicenter evaluations show that AI-assisted dosing matched or exceeded REI performance in 76% of cases, particularly in preventing over-prediction of mature oocytes in high-responders.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Explore our Precision Ovarian Stimulation Protocols.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Integrated Prediction System for Individualised Ovarian Stimulation and OHSS Prevention,” JMIR (2026) / PMID: [41229699].</p>\n<h4><strong>🧬 Metabolic Profiling of SCM: The ‘Secretome’ Update</strong></h4>\n<p>While image-based AI dominates, Spent Culture Media (SCM) analysis is maturing. A 2026 meta-analysis has identified specific low-molecular-weight metabolites that serve as objective biomarkers for embryo viability.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Key Findings:</strong> Seven metabolites were positively associated with implantation, while ten were identified as negative markers. This “metabolic signature” allows for a label-free, non-invasive assessment of the embryo’s developmental competence.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Evidence Level:</strong> Moderate (Technological validation complete; larger prospective trials required for universal clinical adoption).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Discover Santaan’s Advanced Embryology Lab Technology.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “The quest for metabolic biomarkers of IVF outcomes: a meta-analysis,” Frontiers in Cell and Dev. Bio. (2025/2026) / DOI: 10.3389/fcell.2025.1640807.</p>\n<h4><strong>📈 Santaan’s Scientific Leadership</strong></h4>\n<p>At Santaan, we emphasise Explainable AI (XAI). We believe that transparency, showing the clinician the “attribution maps” behind an AI score, is essential for trust. For a deeper technical dive into our U-Net architectures and SCM profiling, visit: Santaan IVF on Medium.</p>\n<p><strong>Connect With Us</strong></p>\n<p><strong>For Clinicians:</strong> Stay at the forefront of reproductive science. Join our digital health collaborative to access real-time AI-driven benchmarks and advanced dose-prediction tools.</p>\n<p>👉 Contact our Clinical Relations Team</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://santaan.in/contact-us\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/contact-us</a></p>\n<p><strong>Technical Metadata</strong></p>",
