    "title": "AI in IVF 2026: Foundation Models, Non-Invasive PGT-A, and Real-Time Follicle Intelligence",
    "excerpt": "Clinical Disclaimer: For clinician education only; not patient-specific medical advice. Welcome to the March 4, 2026, edition of Fertility Insights. As the reproductive landscape s...",
    "html": "<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*pWfp4aMfb2aAoC7q1bbBaw.png\"></figure><p><strong>Clinical Disclaimer:</strong> For clinician education only; not patient-specific medical advice.</p>\n<p>Welcome to the March 4, 2026, edition of Fertility Insights. As the reproductive landscape shifts toward high-precision digital health, Santaan remains committed to translating the latest AI breakthroughs into superior clinical outcomes. Today, we examine the leap from narrow AI to Foundational IVF Models and the clinical validation of automated follicle tracking in global multicenter trials.</p>\n<h4><strong>🔬 Clinical Deep Dive: FEMI- The Foundation Model Era</strong></h4>\n<p>The most significant shift in IVF this year is the transition from task-specific “narrow” AI to Foundational IVF Models for Imaging (FEMI). Unlike previous iterations that required rigid, manual labelling, foundation models utilise Vision Transformer (ViT) architectures pre-trained on approximately 18 million unlabelled time-lapse images.</p>\n<p>• <strong>The Breakthrough:</strong> FEMI employs a self-supervised learning (SSL) approach to rebuild original images from masked inputs, allowing it to capture global context and long-range biological dependencies that local pixel-based CNNs often miss.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Evidence Level:</strong> High (Validated across multiple clinics and tasks, including ploidy prediction, blastulation time, and stage prediction).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Performance:</strong> Recent data indicate that FEMI significantly outperforms benchmark models like VGG16 and ResNet101, particularly in predicting ploidy under conditions of low embryo quality.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “Foundation models in IVF: from speculation to implementation with FEMI.” Hum Reprod. 2025/2026 / PMID: [41220066].</p>\n<h4><strong>🤖 Precision Stimulation: The ‘Digital Twin’ &amp; FOLLISCAN Validation</strong></h4>\n<p>Standardising the “trigger” decision is being solved by automated follicular tracking. The FOLLISCAN multicenter study, recently updated in early 2026, has established a new benchmark for clinical reliability in ovarian stimulation.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Performance Data:</strong> In a study involving 5,508 scans across four international centres, the AI model achieved 98.2% precision (95% CI, 96.5–99.2) for follicles ≥ 10 mm.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Workflow Impact:</strong> Ultrasound annotation time was reduced 2.5-fold, with specialists requiring only 0.54 corrections per scan on average. This reduces inter-operator variability and optimises the retrieval of mature (MII) oocytes.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Explore our Precision IVF Protocols at Santaan.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “An artificial intelligence platform for automated measurement of ovarian follicles: a multicenter study.” JARG (2026) / PMID: [41485151].</p>\n<h4><strong>🧬 Non-Invasive Genetics: Optimising niPGT-A and Predictive Prioritisation</strong></h4>\n<p>While trophectoderm biopsy remains the definitive diagnostic, 2026 is seeing the refinement of Non-Invasive PGT-A (niPGT-A), which analyses cell-free DNA (cfDNA) released into the culture medium.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Clinical Insight:</strong> Recent consensus suggests that niPGT-A performs with approximately 70% accuracy in determining chromosomal normalcy, serving as an effective “triage” to prioritise embryos for transfer without the risks associated with biopsy.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Evidence Level:</strong> Moderate (Ongoing discussion on clinical efficacy versus classical biopsy).</p>\n<p>• <strong>Internal Resource:</strong> Discover our AI-Driven Embryology Lab Technology.</p>\n<p>• <strong>Citation:</strong> “The first AI-assisted IVF babies are now being born.” National Geographic (Dec 2025/March 2026 Update).</p>\n<h4><strong>📈 Santaan’s Scientific Leadership</strong></h4>\n<p>At Santaan, we emphasise the Explainability of AI. Every automated measurement and predictive score is designed to be clinician-verified, ensuring that the “Human-in-the-Loop” remains central to the IVF journey. For a deeper analysis of our technological framework, visit: Santaan IVF on Medium.</p>\n<p><strong>Connect With Us</strong></p>\n<p>For Clinicians: Stay ahead of the technology curve. Are you looking to integrate AI-driven diagnostics into your referral workflow or collaborate on clinical research?</p>\n<p>👉 Contact our Clinical Relations Team</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://santaan.in/contact-us\">https://www.google.com/search?q=https://santaan.in/contact-us</a></p>\n<p><strong>Technical Metadata</strong></p>",
